when the offers were pouring in...

263
00:18:08,319 --> 00:18:11,237
...but I just got
so comfy here and...

264
00:18:11,589 --> 00:18:14,259
I turned down some amazing work.

265
00:18:14,478 --> 00:18:15,723
Like what?

266
00:18:16,878 --> 00:18:19,475
Well, let's just say
if I'd left 15 years ago...

267
00:18:19,835 --> 00:18:24,283
...the landscape of Mexican
cinema would be very different today.

268
00:18:26,376 --> 00:18:28,000
Wow.

269
00:18:29,507 --> 00:18:34,513
But, well, now...
Now's a different time for me.

270
00:18:36,396 --> 00:18:40,359
Oh, hey, come on. Don't do this.

271
00:18:40,676 --> 00:18:42,858
Let me tell you something, okay?

272
00:18:43,146 --> 00:18:47,796
When I watch you do a scene, I'm
thinking, "Boy, she is a great actress."

273
00:18:48,051 --> 00:18:52,642
But I'm also thinking, "She is hot."

274
00:18:55,845 --> 00:18:57,897
You think I'm hot?

275
00:18:59,149 --> 00:19:00,881
You own the room.

276
00:19:05,482 --> 00:19:07,426
We should probably get the...

277
00:19:07,639 --> 00:19:09,750
Oh, yeah. Yeah, we should get...

278
00:19:14,110 --> 00:19:18,072
So when Jessica kisses a man...

279
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:21,753
...she usually puts...

280
00:19:22,077 --> 00:19:25,268
...both her hands on the man's face.

281
00:19:25,521 --> 00:19:28,333
I notice that.
Is that because she's so passionate?

282
00:19:28,548 --> 00:19:31,882
No, it's because that way
the camera only sees her.

283
00:19:35,890 --> 00:19:37,728
You want to try it?

284
00:19:38,012 --> 00:19:39,993
Yeah, okay.

285
00:19:52,242 --> 00:19:54,815
That was good. That was really good.

286
00:19:56,521 --> 00:20:01,907
But I think that maybe your hands are
just a little off. They should be right...

287
00:20:12,421 --> 00:20:14,153
Hey, hey!

288
00:20:15,900 --> 00:20:17,524
Who is it?

289
00:20:18,231 --> 00:20:20,449
It's Tom.
I'm here to pick up the phone.

290
00:20:22,336 --> 00:20:24,768
Why do you get to answer the door?

291
00:20:25,051 --> 00:20:27,589
- Why shouldn't I?
- Because it's my apartment.

292
00:20:27,868 --> 00:20:29,920
Then I get to give him the cell phone.

293
00:20:30,234 --> 00:20:33,603
Okay. Good luck explaining
all the calls to China.

294
00:20:37,854 --> 00:20:39,028
Hi.

295
00:20:43,177 --> 00:20:45,430
Wow, how long were we arguing for?

296
00:20:49,996 --> 00:20:52,250
You're not the man who left the phone.

297
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:55,728
- No, that's my assistant.
- Is he coming?

298
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:57,920
No.

299
00:20:58,241 --> 00:21:00,981
- Could you give us one second?
- Sure.

300
00:21:01,304 --> 00:21:03,450
We'll be right back, sir.

301
00:21:04,992 --> 00:21:08,290
- What do we do?
- I don't know.

302
00:21:08,644 --> 00:21:09,925
Can you believe this?

303
00:21:10,245 --> 00:21:13,305
We were waiting for a hot guy,
and then an even hotter one shows up.

304
00:21:13,620 --> 00:21:14,936
I know.

305
00:21:18,803 --> 00:21:20,357
What?

306
00:21:21,517 --> 00:21:25,159
They just don't make them
like that anymore, you know?

307
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:31,389
No, they do,
but you just have to wait.

308
00:21:33,207 --> 00:21:35,461
Rachel, listen...

309
00:21:35,643 --> 00:21:39,842
...if you let me have him,
then I will really owe you one.

310
00:21:42,497 --> 00:21:44,335
All right.

311
00:21:46,219 --> 00:21:48,508
All right, I will let you have him.

312
00:21:48,898 --> 00:21:50,915
But you owe me. You owe me big.

313
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:54,006
Yeah. You're such a great friend.

314
00:21:55,196 --> 00:21:57,663
Which one of you lovely
ladies am I taking to dinner?

315
00:21:57,979 --> 00:22:00,090
Oh, that'd be me, sir.

316
00:22:01,214 --> 00:22:03,919
- After you.
- Oh, thank you.

317
00:22:04,972 --> 00:22:06,146
Nice.

318
00:22:13,983 --> 00:22:17,282
Well, you certainly own that room.

319
00:22:19,515 --> 00:22:23,370
Actually, I rent the whole place.
I just got what you meant. Thank you.

320
00:22:26,821 --> 00:22:27,960
- Hi.
- Hey.

321
00:22:29,744 --> 00:22:31,096
Oh, my God.

322
00:22:31,727 --> 00:22:33,186
Oh, my God.

323
00:22:33,919 --> 00:22:37,738
Oh, Jessica Lockhart!
In my apartment!

324
00:22:37,954 --> 00:22:41,180
I am such a huge fan.
I am such a huge fan.

325
00:22:41,468 --> 00:22:42,713
It's nice to know...

326
00:22:43,034 --> 00:22:44,350
Monica!

327
00:22:46,304 --> 00:22:48,487
That's my roommate, Rachel.

328
00:22:48,810 --> 00:22:50,755
That explains all
the women's underwear.

329
00:22:51,002 --> 00:22:52,531
Sure.

330
00:22:53,298 --> 00:22:56,358
Oh, my God, it's true!

331
00:22:57,438 --> 00:23:00,772
Oh, my God, you are so amazing.

332
00:23:01,613 --> 00:23:04,911
Can I just ask you to do me
just one favor?

333
00:23:05,127 --> 00:23:06,515
Certainly.

334
00:23:06,866 --> 00:23:09,536
Would you slap me
right here in the face?

335
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:15,282
I'd love to, but my lawyer said
I can't do that anymore.

336
00:23:16,365 --> 00:23:19,769
God, you seem really, really nice.

337
00:23:20,053 --> 00:23:22,270
Okay, bye-bye.

338
00:23:23,080 --> 00:23:26,626
I mean, not fake at all
like most famous people.

339
00:23:26,836 --> 00:23:28,496
All right, here we go.

340
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:30,872
No, wait. Just one more thing.

341
00:23:33,065 --> 00:23:36,540
- You're a stupid bitch.
- I really can't slap you.

342
00:23:36,753 --> 00:23:39,350
- You are so beautiful.
- So nice to meet you.

343
00:23:39,571 --> 00:23:42,975
- My God, you're great.
- Thanks for stopping by.

344
00:23:44,928 --> 00:23:47,182
- I am so sorry about that.
- Oh, no.

345
00:23:47,469 --> 00:23:50,280
Being adored, I'm used to it.
Don't worry about it.

346
00:23:51,574 --> 00:23:52,997
- Oh, my God.
- What?

347
00:23:53,453 --> 00:23:56,157
They sent me today's script.
They never send me the script.

348
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,591
- They don't?
- I'm just in a coma.

349
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:01,276
This must mean I have lines.

350
00:24:05,317 --> 00:24:07,298
How does it happen?

351
00:24:11,335 --> 00:24:15,013
You get thrown from a horse
into an electric fence.

352
00:24:16,936 --> 00:24:19,083
A what? Jessica hates horses.

353
00:24:19,408 --> 00:24:23,405
After this, she's not gonna be crazy
about electricity either.

354
00:24:27,618 --> 00:24:31,437
Now, remember,
you have to imagine me in a kilt.

355
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:36,836
I can imagine you in a short
plaid skirt and knee socks.

356
00:24:37,986 --> 00:24:40,940
- You wanna start telling secrets?
- No.

357
00:24:44,492 --> 00:24:46,568
Now, remember...

358
00:24:46,788 --> 00:24:48,864
...I'm still learning.

359
00:24:57,887 --> 00:25:00,425
One, two, three, four!

360
00:25:18,345 --> 00:25:20,918
You know the song. Sing along.

361
00:25:47,465 --> 00:25:48,853
So?

362
00:25:49,413 --> 00:25:50,729
- No.
- No.

363
00:25:55,223 --> 00:25:58,769
Loosening the saddle on Mother's horse
was brilliant, Fredrick.

364
00:25:59,085 --> 00:26:01,623
And the electric fence, inspired.

365
00:26:01,938 --> 00:26:03,254
Thank you, sweetheart.

366
00:26:04,374 --> 00:26:06,806
I can't believe she's really gone.

367
00:26:07,401 --> 00:26:10,663
Look around you. All of this is ours.

368
00:26:12,620 --> 00:26:14,244
I don't think so.

369
00:26:19,682 --> 00:26:20,690
Who are you?

370
00:26:21,004 --> 00:26:22,772
What's the matter, Dina?

371
00:26:23,022 --> 00:26:25,655
Don't you recognize your own...

372
00:26:26,014 --> 00:26:27,367
...mother?

373
00:26:30,328 --> 00:26:32,961
Cut! That was great, everybody.
Thank you.

374
00:26:33,251 --> 00:26:35,682
That was so wonderful!

375
00:26:35,999 --> 00:26:39,226
I think that you're a better
Jessica than I ever was.

376
00:26:39,583 --> 00:26:42,359
- Oh, no.
- Of course not, but you were good.

377
00:26:42,645 --> 00:26:43,676
Thanks.

378
00:26:44,037 --> 00:26:46,113
Good news. I got another job.

379
00:26:46,437 --> 00:26:48,726
Great. Hey, all right! What is it?

380
00:26:49,081 --> 00:26:51,193
A film in Guadalajara.

381
00:26:52,351 --> 00:26:53,881
The airport?

382
00:26:56,109 --> 00:26:57,461
No, that's LaGuardia.

383
00:27:01,224 --> 00:27:04,522
- This is Mexico.
- Oh, wow.

384
00:27:04,807 --> 00:27:07,025
Well, how long will you be gone?

385
00:27:07,312 --> 00:27:09,044
Eight months.

386
00:27:10,060 --> 00:27:13,666
- That's a really long time.
- Yeah, but you could come and visit.

387
00:27:13,957 --> 00:27:18,156
I bet that you could own
a few places down there.

388
00:27:19,037 --> 00:27:23,106
Oh, you know, I should probably
buy a place in the city first.

389
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,662
And I just got what you meant.
That is...

390
00:27:27,978 --> 00:27:30,161
- That's a tricky one.
- It's tricky.

391
00:27:32,362 --> 00:27:35,244
Joey, I really want to thank you.

392
00:27:35,459 --> 00:27:41,544
You made a very difficult time for me
a little less painful.

393
00:27:43,078 --> 00:27:44,086
Good luck.

394
00:27:45,095 --> 00:27:46,554
You too.

